HEADWORD: Papion
<hw>Pa"pi*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. from native
name: cf. Sp. <ets>papion</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A West
African baboon (<spn>Cynocephalus sphinx</spn>), allied to the chacma.
Its color is generally chestnut, varying in tint.</def>⟦br⟧
